  "type": "clothing",
  "img": "systems/cyberpunk-red-core/icons/compendium/default/Default_Clothing.svg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A formal suit of some kind, but make no mistake - if you're looking for the tucked shirts and clip-on ties of a cube farm, look into Generic Chic. This stuff looks sharp - like it's worth every eddy spent on it. Like it could puncture the hull of a Militech Warlord-class assault carrier, leaving hundreds to drown at sea. Because it's so sharp.</p><p>While wearing the outfit:</p><ul><li><p>The wearer is unmistakably a corpo;</p></li><li><p>They gain <strong>+2 to Accounting, Bureaucracy, Business, Interrogation, and Trading</strong> rolls;</p></li><li><p>They gain <strong>+3 to Wardrobe &amp; Style </strong>rolls;</p></li><li><p>And they suffer <strong>-2 to Local Expert, Persuasion, Bribery, and Conversation</strong> rolls against anyone or anything not affiliated with the corporate elite. Fucking corp rats - stay in your hole!</p></li></ul>"
    },
